comment: Outdoor and return air damper position modulation sequence for multi zone VAV AHU

parameters.name: uMin
parameters.comment: Lower limit of controller input when outdoor damper opens (see diagram)

parameters.name: uMax
parameters.comment: Upper limit of controller input when return damper is closed (see diagram)

parameters.name: uOutDamMax
parameters.comment: Maximum loop signal for the OA damper to be fully open

parameters.name: uRetDamMin
parameters.comment: Minimum loop signal for the RA damper to be fully open

parameters.name: samplePeriod
parameters.comment: Sample period of component, used to limit the rate of change of the dampers (to avoid quick opening that can result in frost)

inputs.name: uTSup
inputs.comment: Signal for supply air temperature control (T Sup Control Loop Signal in diagram)

inputs.name: uOutDamPosMin
inputs.comment: Minimum economizer damper position limit as returned by the damper position limits  sequence

inputs.name: uOutDamPosMax
inputs.comment:
Maximum economizer damper position limit as returned by the economizer enable-disable sequence.
    If the economizer is disabled, this value equals uOutDamPosMin

inputs.name: uRetDamPosMin
inputs.comment: Minimum return air damper position limit as returned by the economizer enable-disable sequence

inputs.name: uRetDamPosMax
inputs.comment: Maximum return air damper position limit as returned by the economizer enable-disable sequence

models.name: outDamMinLimSig
models.comment: Minimal control loop signal for the outdoor air damper

models.name: outDamMaxLimSig
models.comment: Maximum control loop signal for the outdoor air damper

models.name: retDamConMinLimSig
models.comment: Minimal control loop signal for the return air damper

models.name: retDamMaxLimSig
models.comment: Maximal control loop signal for the return air damper

models.name: outDamPos
models.comment: Damper position is linearly proportional to the control signal between signal limits

models.name: retDamPos
models.comment: Damper position is linearly proportional to the control signal between signal limits

models.name: firOrdHolOutDam
models.comment: First order hold to avoid too fast opening/closing of damper (which may cause freeze protection to be too slow to compensate)

models.name: firOrdHolRetDam
models.comment: First order hold to avoid too fast opening/closing of damper (which may cause freeze protection to be too slow to compensate)

info:
This is a multi zone VAV AHU economizer modulation block. It calculates the outdoor and return air damper positions based on the supply air temperature control loop signal. The implementation is in line with ASHRAE Guidline 36 (G36), PART5.N.2.c. Damper positions are linearly mapped to the supply air control loop signal. This is a final sequence in the composite multi zone VAV AHU economizer control sequence. Damper position limits, which are the inputs to the sequence, are the outputs of Buildings.Controls.OBC.ASHRAE.G36_PR1.AHUs.MultiZone.VAV.Economizers.Subsequences.Limits and Buildings.Controls.OBC.ASHRAE.G36_PR1.AHUs.MultiZone.VAV.Economizers.Subsequences.Enable sequences.

When the economizer is enabled, the PI controller modulates the damper positions. Return and outdoor damper are not interlocked. When the economizer is disabled, the damper positions are set to the minimum outdoor air damper position limits.

The time rate of change of the damper signals is limited by a first order hold, using the sample time samplePeriod. This prevents a quick opening of the outdoor air damper, for example when the outdoor airflow setpoint has a step change. Slowing down the opening of the outdoor air damper allows the freeze protection to componensate with its dynamics that is faster than the opening of the outdoor air damper. To avoid that all dampers are closed, the return air damper has the same time rate of change limitation.

The control charts below show the input-output structure and an economizer damper modulation sequence assuming a well configured controller. Control diagram:

comment: Output the value of the input x along a line specified by two points

parameters.name: limitBelow
parameters.comment: If true, limit input u to be no smaller than x1

parameters.name: limitAbove
parameters.comment: If true, limit input u to be no larger than x2

inputs.name: x1
inputs.comment: Support point x1, with x1 < x2

inputs.name: x2
inputs.comment: Support point x2, with x2 > x1

outputs.name: y
outputs.comment: f(x) along the line specified by (x1, f1) and (x2, f2)

models.name: xLim
models.comment: Input value after applying the limits

info:
Block that outputs y = a + b u, where u is an input and the coefficients a and b are determined so that the line intercepts the two input points specified by the two points x1 and f1, and x2 and f2.

The parameters limitBelow and limitAbove determine whether x1 and x2 are also used to limit the input u.

If the limits are used, then this block requires x1 < x2.
